com.analog.lyric.options

Interface IOptionKey<T extends java.io.Serializable>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - is the type of the value that will be associated with the key. The type should either be String, a wrapped primitive type (e.g. Double, Boolean), or an immutable concrete implementation of IOptionValue.

    Concrete instances should be public static final fields, with given name(), preferably in a subclass of OptionKeyDeclarer.

    OptionKey contains useful static methods for loading option keys, whether or not they are implemented as subclasses of that class.

    All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BooleanOptionKey, ClassOptionKey, ConstructorOptionKey, DoubleListOptionKey, DoubleOptionKey, DoubleRangeOptionKey, EnumOptionKey, GenericOptionKey, GenericSamplerOptionKey, IntegerListOptionKey, IntegerOptionKey, LongOptionKey, OptionKey, ProposalKernelOptionKey, StringListOptionKey, StringOptionKey, VariableEliminatorCostListOptionKey

    @Immutable
public interface IOptionKey<T extends java.io.Serializable>
extends java.io.Serializable
    A unique key for looking up or setting a value from a IOptionHolder.

    See Also:
    OptionKey.forCanonicalName(java.lang.String), OptionKey.inClass(Class, String), OptionKey.canonicalName(IOptionKey), OptionKey.qualifiedName(IOptionKey)

      • convertToExternal

        @Nullable
java.lang.Object convertToExternal(T value)
        Converts value to an external representation

        Converts value to representation suitable for use in external environments such as MATLAB or Python. Acceptable output types include boxed primitive types, Strings, and arrays of the those.

        It is expected that the returned value can be converted back to the original typed value using convertToValue(java.lang.Object).

        Parameters:
        value -
        Since:
        0.07

      • validate

        T validate(T value,
         @Nullable
         IOptionHolder optionHolder)
        Validates value for this key.

        This is invoked by implementations of IOptionHolder.setOption(com.analog.lyric.options.IOptionKey<T>, T) and can be overridden to put extra constraints on the value.

        Parameters:
        value - is the value to be set on this option.
        optionHolder - is the option holder on which the option is being set, if available.
        Returns:
        the value itself if valid otherwise throws an exception.
        Throws:

        OptionValidationException - if value is invalid.
